# Sub-CA atomic-state-write race (DETECTED — investigation surfaced)
@sub-CA-finding /tmp/.hexa-runtime/cache_err.*.tmp filled with 'mv: /Users/ghost/.hive/subagent-state/state.swap: No such file or directory' (hundreds of lines).
@sub-CA-location /Users/ghost/core/hive/tool/subagent_dispatch.hexa lines 920-927 — `awk … > path.swap && mv path.swap path` pattern.
@sub-CA-race 30 concurrent kick chains all writing to ~/.hive/subagent-state/state.swap and racing to mv. One winner per cycle, 29 losers. 0-byte state file + missing state.swap = symptom.
@sub-CA-impact stuck procs spin in error loop indefinitely. Likely contributor to Mac saturation (Sub-BR DEFER) + hexa_remote rc=64 (subagent never reaches success path).
@sub-CA-fix-direction per-pid swap suffix (.swap.$$) eliminates race. Or flock on state file. Must be careful to preserve atomicity. DEFERRED — risky edit during active /loop session.

